WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

2
00:01:07.025 --> 00:01:08.110
<i>When I was a child.</i>

3
00:01:08.151 --> 00:01:09.820
<i>my mother would tell me a story</i>

4
00:01:09.862 --> 00:01:12.155
<i>about how the Devil foams the Earth.</i>

5
00:01:14.366 --> 00:01:17.661
<i>Sometimes. she said.
he would take human form</i>

6
00:01:17.703 --> 00:01:21.290
<i>so he could punish the damned on Earth
before claiming their souls.</i>

7
00:01:23.667 --> 00:01:25.878
<i>The ones he chose
would be gathered together</i>

8
00:01:25.961 --> 00:01:30.883
<i>and tortured as he hid amongst them.
pretending to be one of them.</i>

9
00:01:32.342 --> 00:01:35.679
<i>I always believed my mother
was telling me an old wives' tale.</i>

10
00:03:33.088 --> 00:03:36.091
<i>My mother's story
would always begin the same way.</i>

11
00:03:36.216 --> 00:03:40.179
<i>with a suicide paving the way
for the Devil's arrival.</i>

12
00:03:43.891 --> 00:03:47.978
<i>And it would always end
with the deaths of all those trapped.</i>

13
00:04:07.998 --> 00:04:10.542
<i>I'm good. I feel good.
I feel amazing.</i>

14
00:04:12.961 --> 00:04:15.464
You know the main reason
why people go back to drinking?

15
00:04:15.506 --> 00:04:16.548
No.

16
00:04:16.632 --> 00:04:17.633
Guess.

17
00:04:18.091 --> 00:04:19.593
The Eagles.

18
00:04:20.302 --> 00:04:21.512
Resentment.

19
00:04:22.137 --> 00:04:24.806
Are we seriously
talking about this again?

20
00:04:24.973 --> 00:04:26.350
It's important.

21
00:04:26.475 --> 00:04:28.310
Your ability to forgive
is gonna determine

22
00:04:28.352 --> 00:04:31.855
the quality of the rest of your life
more than anything else.

23
00:04:33.565 --> 00:04:35.943
Look. some things
are beyond forgiveness.

24
00:04:36.235 --> 00:04:37.694
You're already on your way.

25
00:04:37.736 --> 00:04:39.404
You've taken responsibility
for your actions.

26
00:04:39.488 --> 00:04:41.448
That's more than
half the battle right there.

27
00:04:41.907 --> 00:04:43.450
But to truly feel free.

28
00:04:45.827 --> 00:04:47.538
you may need
to finally start believing

29
00:04:47.579 --> 00:04:49.540
in something greater than yourself.

30
00:04:50.082 --> 00:04:51.375
That sounds good.

31
00:04:53.293 --> 00:04:54.628
It does.

32
00:04:55.420 --> 00:04:58.590
But when I think about
the guy that killed my family.

33
00:05:00.008 --> 00:05:02.719
I have a tough time believing in
much of anything.

34
00:05:03.428 --> 00:05:06.765
I'm just saying.
leave yourself open to it.

35
00:05:07.683 --> 00:05:11.395
Can we just have breakfast for once?

36
00:05:11.728 --> 00:05:13.021
Talk about normal stuff.

37
00:05:13.063 --> 00:05:14.690
I'm your sponsor.
You can talk about normal stuff

38
00:05:14.731 --> 00:05:15.858
with everybody else.

39
00:05:22.364 --> 00:05:25.075
Hey. Got a good one for you.

40
00:05:25.117 --> 00:05:26.201
Yeah?

41
00:05:50.893 --> 00:05:52.186
Yeah. it doesn't make sense. right?

42
00:05:52.895 --> 00:05:55.981
A guy hits a truck with this kind of force
from a two-story building?

43
00:05:56.064 --> 00:05:57.733
Definitely a jumper.

44
00:05:57.858 --> 00:05:59.193
Are you sure he wasn't thrown?

45
00:05:59.276 --> 00:06:01.278
He's got a rosary in his hand.

46
00:06:02.613 --> 00:06:05.199
Not the kind of thing
you grab in a panic.

47
00:06:05.490 --> 00:06:06.617
Right.

48
00:06:10.746 --> 00:06:12.164
- Elsa.
- Bowden.

49
00:06:12.539 --> 00:06:13.540
Hi.

50
00:06:27.471 --> 00:06:29.723
There's no glass on the ground.

51
00:06:30.098 --> 00:06:33.852
The truck wasn't here when he made impact.
It must have rolled.

52
00:06:34.853 --> 00:06:35.938
Uh-huh.

53
00:06:42.277 --> 00:06:44.613
Your guy jumped from that building.

54
00:06:45.113 --> 00:06:47.491
And what? Your dead guy
turned the corner. here?

55
00:06:50.619 --> 00:06:52.704
These things are made
to bounce trucks off.

56
00:06:55.290 --> 00:06:56.917
You got to be kidding me.

57
00:06:57.292 --> 00:06:58.877
Let's walk it.

58
00:06:58.961 --> 00:07:00.128
Yeah.

59
00:07:37.875 --> 00:07:39.126
Larson.

60
00:07:53.765 --> 00:07:55.684
Hey! Hey. lady.
you got to sign in.

61
00:07:55.976 --> 00:07:57.811
Oh. Where's Ramsey?
He knows me.

62
00:07:57.978 --> 00:07:59.730
Ramsey's out sick.
You got me.

63
00:07:59.813 --> 00:08:01.565
And that means you gotta sign in.

64
00:08:03.192 --> 00:08:05.569
I mean. do I look like such a threat?

65
00:08:06.236 --> 00:08:09.573
Don't blame me.
They got procedures.

66
00:08:11.074 --> 00:08:12.993
Keep dreaming. dawg.

67
00:08:17.915 --> 00:08:20.209
You have to cover the sign in.

68
00:08:20.250 --> 00:08:22.503
Some lawyers on 39
need this right away.

69
00:08:22.711 --> 00:08:24.671
You're not taking the stairs again.

70
00:08:24.713 --> 00:08:26.215
What else am I gonna do
to stay in shape?

71
00:08:26.381 --> 00:08:29.092
To 39?
Just get on the damn elevator.

72
00:08:32.179 --> 00:08:33.222
Come in.

73
00:08:33.263 --> 00:08:34.598
It's too tight for me.

74
00:08:34.765 --> 00:08:35.974
You can squeeze in.

75
00:08:36.058 --> 00:08:37.184
No.

76
00:08:54.785 --> 00:08:56.662
Hold. please.

77
00:08:58.372 --> 00:08:59.706
Thank you.

78
00:09:00.082 --> 00:09:01.875
Forty-two. please.

79
00:09:01.917 --> 00:09:02.960
You bet.

80
00:09:03.293 --> 00:09:04.962
Now. see. this I can do.

81
00:09:05.671 --> 00:09:06.797
Could you hold that?

82
00:09:06.839 --> 00:09:07.881
Uh. Sorry.

83
00:09:09.925 --> 00:09:11.260
Thanks for your help.

84
00:09:11.385 --> 00:09:12.761
Don't mention it.

85
00:09:55.804 --> 00:09:57.514
Uh-uh. this is not good.

86
00:09:58.432 --> 00:10:00.100
Oh. come on. man.

87
00:10:00.184 --> 00:10:01.768
Don't do this.

88
00:10:14.156 --> 00:10:16.158
Come on. Timonen.
put a stick on it.

89
00:10:16.491 --> 00:10:17.701
How we doing?

90
00:10:17.784 --> 00:10:19.620
Same score.

91
00:10:21.663 --> 00:10:23.373
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

92
00:10:28.795 --> 00:10:31.298
Why is elevator six
in inspection mode?

93
00:10:32.132 --> 00:10:34.092
- Huh?
- Elevator six.

94
00:10:38.931 --> 00:10:41.934
A full house.
Two queens. three jacks.

95
00:10:46.104 --> 00:10:47.606
- Call Dwight.
- Yeah.

96
00:10:48.190 --> 00:10:49.566
Yo. Dwight. you got a problem.

97
00:10:50.692 --> 00:10:53.862
Tell me about it.
I'm already up on 35 fixing it.

98
00:10:54.363 --> 00:10:55.906
The elevator?

99
00:10:56.031 --> 00:10:57.616
<i>No. the broken window.</i>

100
00:10:58.033 --> 00:10:59.326
You're not fixing the elevator?

101
00:10:59.368 --> 00:11:01.411
Screen says six is on inspection mode.

102
00:11:01.495 --> 00:11:02.829
<i>We got people stuck in there.</i>

103
00:11:02.871 --> 00:11:04.164
Are you sure
you're reading that right?

104
00:11:04.206 --> 00:11:06.250
<i>Your eyes ain't
what they used to be.</i>

105
00:11:07.334 --> 00:11:09.086
You know what?
I'll ask your mom to read it for me

106
00:11:09.127 --> 00:11:11.922
next time I got her
bent over the console.

107
00:11:12.714 --> 00:11:14.925
<i>My mom's 78. Have at it.</i>

108
00:11:14.967 --> 00:11:16.093
Ooh!

109
00:11:16.677 --> 00:11:18.345
Yeah. Listen. buddy.
just go up to the machine room

110
00:11:18.387 --> 00:11:20.013
and check it out. okay?

111
00:11:20.222 --> 00:11:21.473
<i>On my way.</i>

112
00:11:37.865 --> 00:11:39.867
Just trying to get something
to jump-start it.

113
00:11:39.908 --> 00:11:42.327
Don't you have emergency procedures?

114
00:11:43.662 --> 00:11:45.789
I don't know. I'm just a temp.
I just started working here.

115
00:11:46.206 --> 00:11:48.208
Well. don't you service these things?

116
00:11:48.500 --> 00:11:50.586
Try hitting the emergency button.

117
00:11:56.592 --> 00:11:59.011
Don't you keep up your equipment?

118
00:12:00.721 --> 00:12:02.723
I don't know.
Like I said--

119
00:12:02.806 --> 00:12:04.099
Don't you have a walkie-talkie?

120
00:12:04.266 --> 00:12:06.852
No. I didn't think I'd need it.

121
00:12:06.935 --> 00:12:08.770
- Don't you think it would have been--
- Won't you shut up?

122
00:12:08.812 --> 00:12:10.105
Yeah. take it easy.

123
00:12:10.439 --> 00:12:11.899
I mean. seriously!

124
00:12:12.065 --> 00:12:13.442
You don't have a walkie-talkie?

125
00:12:14.026 --> 00:12:15.569
<i>Hey. people. we see you in there.</i>

126
00:12:15.611 --> 00:12:16.653
We're stuck!

127
00:12:16.737 --> 00:12:19.364
<i>Hang tough. we got the
building engineer on his way.</i>

128
00:12:19.489 --> 00:12:22.159
When was the last time you heard
somebody say "hang tough"?

129
00:12:22.326 --> 00:12:24.161
- <i>What did you say?</i>
- Nothing.

130
00:12:24.244 --> 00:12:25.913
- <i>What did you say?</i>
- Nothing.

131
00:12:26.288 --> 00:12:27.581
Is he picking a fight?

132
00:12:27.664 --> 00:12:29.750
<i>Can one of you look
towards the camera</i>

133
00:12:29.791 --> 00:12:32.294
<i>and say something
loud and clear. please?</i>

134
00:12:33.795 --> 00:12:37.216
Your building sucks!

135
00:12:37.966 --> 00:12:39.051
I can't hear you.

136
00:12:39.134 --> 00:12:41.178
The speaker in the car is supposed
to let us talk both ways.

137
00:12:41.303 --> 00:12:42.513
but you can hear me?

138
00:12:42.554 --> 00:12:44.056
It's working on this end. yeah!

139
00:12:44.139 --> 00:12:45.766
He just said he can't hear us.

140
00:12:45.807 --> 00:12:47.434
didn't say we should talk louder.

141
00:12:47.559 --> 00:12:50.270
<i>Okay. um. give us a sec.</i>

142
00:12:50.729 --> 00:12:53.023
Well. this is reassuring.

143
00:12:56.360 --> 00:12:58.028
I got to be somewhere.

144
00:13:02.241 --> 00:13:03.992
You're not gonna get
a signal in here.

145
00:13:04.326 --> 00:13:07.704
I just need to call my job
so I don't get fired over this.

146
00:13:09.540 --> 00:13:11.208
Typical bullshit.

147
00:13:11.500 --> 00:13:13.210
Do any of y'all have a signal?

148
00:13:13.502 --> 00:13:14.878
I've got one bar.

149
00:13:30.185 --> 00:13:32.896
Hello? This is Larson.

150
00:13:33.772 --> 00:13:37.109
Can you please connect me
to my job at the security desk?

151
00:13:38.527 --> 00:13:39.653
Can you hear me?

152
00:13:39.695 --> 00:13:41.738
Tell them to get us out of here!

153
00:13:42.322 --> 00:13:43.490
Hello?

154
00:13:48.787 --> 00:13:50.873
They'll just have to deal.

155
00:13:51.832 --> 00:13:53.750
Well. at least we got tunes.

156
00:13:54.918 --> 00:13:58.839
<i>Don't sit under that apple tree
with anyone else but me</i>

157
00:13:58.881 --> 00:13:59.882
Come on. grandma.
you know the words.

158
00:14:00.215 --> 00:14:01.717
<i>Anyone else but me</i>

159
00:14:01.758 --> 00:14:03.427
Don't be a jerk.

160
00:14:04.011 --> 00:14:06.972
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry. Miss Manners.

161
00:14:07.055 --> 00:14:09.057
Did I offend your noble sensibilities?

162
00:14:09.141 --> 00:14:10.267
Why don't you lay off. pal?

163
00:14:10.350 --> 00:14:11.894
Why don't you suck a butt?

164
00:14:12.811 --> 00:14:13.937
This is great.

165
00:14:14.188 --> 00:14:16.565
Let's just pick on the nice guy
for bringing a little levity.

166
00:14:16.982 --> 00:14:20.736
Maybe we should all
just stop talking for a while.

167
00:14:21.486 --> 00:14:22.654
Sure.

168
00:14:29.411 --> 00:14:33.540
Okay. I was just joking.
I'm joking.

169
00:14:58.607 --> 00:14:59.900
<i>Hey. Dwight. are you there yet?</i>

170
00:14:59.942 --> 00:15:00.943
Almost.

171
00:15:04.279 --> 00:15:05.948
Hey. look. man.
I'm just glad you're dating again.

172
00:15:05.989 --> 00:15:07.324
I'm just glad you're glad.

173
00:15:07.741 --> 00:15:11.495
You know what I meant.
You know. after all your troubles--

174
00:15:11.537 --> 00:15:13.205
I know what you meant.

175
00:15:14.456 --> 00:15:16.959
So. how's that been going for you?

176
00:15:17.042 --> 00:15:18.126
Good.

177
00:15:18.168 --> 00:15:20.003
Ninety days tomorrow.

178
00:15:20.420 --> 00:15:22.256
Wow. 90 days!

179
00:15:22.339 --> 00:15:23.882
It seems like just yesterday
since we--

180
00:15:23.966 --> 00:15:25.634
Not to me. it doesn't.

181
00:15:35.894 --> 00:15:38.397
You wouldn't happen to have
a broken window up there. would you?

182
00:15:38.438 --> 00:15:39.690
Yeah.

183
00:15:40.816 --> 00:15:42.317
Facing this direction?

184
00:15:42.568 --> 00:15:43.777
Mmm-hmm.

185
00:15:44.027 --> 00:15:46.071
Big enough to fit a person through it?

186
00:15:46.488 --> 00:15:47.990
I suppose.

187
00:15:49.032 --> 00:15:50.158
Please stop sweeping.

188
00:15:50.325 --> 00:15:52.703
I'm declaring this a crime scene.

189
00:15:53.453 --> 00:15:54.913
Car 602.

190
00:15:55.831 --> 00:15:57.207
What the hell is that?

191
00:15:57.583 --> 00:15:58.584
Look out!

192
00:16:03.463 --> 00:16:04.631
You might want to secure that better.

193
00:16:04.673 --> 00:16:05.841
Okay. okay!

194
00:16:06.258 --> 00:16:08.802
<i>In her story.
innocent people always die.</i>

195
00:16:10.220 --> 00:16:12.222
<i>Poor souls just trying to help out.</i>

196
00:16:12.306 --> 00:16:14.725
<i>who didn't realize what
they were dealing with.</i>

197
00:16:15.684 --> 00:16:18.687
<i>He doesn't take kindly
to those who stand in his way.</i>

198
00:16:21.356 --> 00:16:22.941
Hey. old man.

199
00:16:23.066 --> 00:16:25.819
It doesn't say inspection mode here.
Circuits look fine.

200
00:16:26.028 --> 00:16:27.779
<i>Okay. Try flipping elevator six.</i>

201
00:16:27.863 --> 00:16:30.699
<i>I'll tell the people in the car.
You count to 20. then do it.</i>

202
00:16:30.741 --> 00:16:31.909
Cool.

203
00:16:33.535 --> 00:16:38.624
"Inspected and certified
August 12 by G. Carson."

204
00:16:39.708 --> 00:16:42.544
Hey. what do you say we go visit
G. Carson when we're out of here?

205
00:16:42.586 --> 00:16:44.880
Tell him what we think
of his inspecting prowess.

206
00:16:45.589 --> 00:16:48.008
<i>People. we're gonna flip
off the lights for one sec</i>

207
00:16:48.050 --> 00:16:49.426
<i>to see if there's
a short in the breaker.</i>

208
00:16:49.468 --> 00:16:50.761
You're gonna cut off the power?

209
00:16:50.886 --> 00:16:52.387
Does that mean we could drop?

210
00:16:52.554 --> 00:16:54.056
<i>You'll be fine.
I just didn't want you to--</i>

211
00:16:55.015 --> 00:16:56.016
- What's happening?
- Come on!

212
00:16:56.058 --> 00:16:58.310
Nothing. Nothing. Just relax.

213
00:17:00.687 --> 00:17:01.730
Come on.

214
00:17:01.772 --> 00:17:03.065
Get off me!

215
00:17:04.149 --> 00:17:05.776
Get off me!

216
00:17:06.693 --> 00:17:07.945
Sorry.

217
00:17:13.283 --> 00:17:15.118
What's wrong with you. man?

218
00:17:21.333 --> 00:17:23.502
When I was younger.
my brother locked me in a trunk

219
00:17:23.585 --> 00:17:24.920
for six hours.

220
00:17:25.295 --> 00:17:27.422
I have trouble with tight spaces.

221
00:17:27.881 --> 00:17:29.633
Oh. great.

222
00:17:44.273 --> 00:17:45.315
Come on.

223
00:17:59.955 --> 00:18:01.123
Can we get out through that?

224
00:18:01.164 --> 00:18:03.250
What are you gonna do?
Shimmy up the cables?

225
00:18:04.501 --> 00:18:06.044
You'll be a lot safer in here.

226
00:18:07.004 --> 00:18:09.298
Anybody know where the
bathroom is in this thing?

227
00:18:10.174 --> 00:18:11.592
Did it work?

228
00:18:11.717 --> 00:18:13.177
<i>Nope. they're still stuck.</i>

229
00:18:14.052 --> 00:18:16.471
Let me go check the mains
in the basement.

230
00:18:23.020 --> 00:18:25.230
<i>All right. thanks a lot.
Wow.</i>

231
00:18:26.148 --> 00:18:27.357
What's going on?

232
00:18:28.066 --> 00:18:29.359
You know that window on 35?

233
00:18:29.443 --> 00:18:30.485
Yeah.

234
00:18:30.569 --> 00:18:32.821
Looks like somebody might
have jumped through it.

235
00:18:34.907 --> 00:18:36.116
Today?

236
00:18:36.241 --> 00:18:37.492
Yeah. This morning.

237
00:18:40.370 --> 00:18:42.080
<i>Thanks for bearing with us. people.</i>

238
00:18:42.164 --> 00:18:44.666
<i>We should get you back on line
in a few minutes.</i>

239
00:18:44.833 --> 00:18:46.084
It's been minutes.

240
00:18:46.168 --> 00:18:48.003
How long is it going to take?

241
00:18:54.218 --> 00:18:57.137
When we get out of here.
you're gonna need a good rest.

242
00:18:58.430 --> 00:18:59.765
"Mattress Mania"?

243
00:19:00.182 --> 00:19:04.436
That's us. Everybody's had
their mattress too long. Am I right?

244
00:19:04.728 --> 00:19:08.732
You didn't follow that advice
about flipping it every few months

245
00:19:09.191 --> 00:19:11.568
and now you've worn
a groove into it.

246
00:19:11.610 --> 00:19:13.904
and you think.
"Well. I'm used to it.

247
00:19:13.987 --> 00:19:16.365
"So. hey.
But I do miss the way it felt

248
00:19:16.406 --> 00:19:18.283
"when it came fresh
out of that bag."

249
00:19:19.117 --> 00:19:21.411
Look at those shoes.
they've been through the mill.

250
00:19:21.578 --> 00:19:25.916
They're saying. "Someone deserves
a better place to lie down."

251
00:19:26.208 --> 00:19:27.876
Are you insulting my shoes?

252
00:19:28.126 --> 00:19:32.089
The point is. a new mattress
will cost a lot less than you think.

253
00:19:32.548 --> 00:19:34.925
You don't have to be
as well-off as this one.

254
00:19:35.217 --> 00:19:37.135
I'm not that well-off.

255
