to fight him with force.</i>

516
00:34:52.843 --> 00:34:55.429
<i>but some battles
can't be fought with weapons.</i>

517
00:34:55.679 --> 00:34:56.972
<i>Will you all please clear a space<i>

518
00:34:57.014 --> 00:34:58.223
between the camera and the body

519
00:34:58.307 --> 00:34:59.308
so I can see him?

520
00:35:00.309 --> 00:35:03.312
Don't touch the body.
This is a crime scene now.

521
00:35:03.437 --> 00:35:04.646
Though I know you're stuck in there.

522
00:35:04.688 --> 00:35:06.481
I expect you to do
as little damage to it

523
00:35:06.523 --> 00:35:08.275
as humanly possible. got it?

524
00:35:09.693 --> 00:35:10.986
Any luck with the elevator company?

525
00:35:11.111 --> 00:35:12.362
They're out of business.

526
00:35:13.822 --> 00:35:15.532
I guess that figures.

527
00:35:16.992 --> 00:35:19.203
A shard of glass sliced up
and into the jugular.

528
00:35:19.286 --> 00:35:20.954
This is definitely not an accident.

529
00:35:25.459 --> 00:35:28.712
Who chooses a contained room
with three witnesses for a killing?

530
00:35:29.004 --> 00:35:31.590
Unless they're so worked up.
they can't control themselves.

531
00:35:32.216 --> 00:35:35.344
These people are shook up.
but they don't look murderous.

532
00:35:37.012 --> 00:35:38.514
I'm missing something here.

533
00:35:45.979 --> 00:35:48.023
I need a volunteer to help me out.

534
00:35:53.695 --> 00:35:55.739
<i>There's a piece of paper
hanging out of his pocket.</i>

535
00:35:55.864 --> 00:35:58.951
<i>Very carefully. I want you to take it out
and hold it up to the camera.</i>

536
00:36:16.593 --> 00:36:19.596
"Vince." It looks like "McCormick."

537
00:36:19.721 --> 00:36:22.015
The return address is
for the Better Business Bureau.

538
00:36:22.140 --> 00:36:23.725
They have an office on 35.

539
00:36:24.560 --> 00:36:26.144
- You got a freight elevator?
- Yeah.

540
00:36:37.239 --> 00:36:39.950
I've never seen a person die.

541
00:36:42.911 --> 00:36:44.621
Neither have I.

542
00:36:45.706 --> 00:36:47.332
It's pretty awful. huh?

543
00:36:49.585 --> 00:36:51.086
So. what. you have?

544
00:36:53.755 --> 00:36:56.258
Yeah. I spent some time in Afghanistan.

545
00:36:58.594 --> 00:37:01.013
You see some things
you wish you hadn't.

546
00:37:03.265 --> 00:37:05.267
Wait. so you've been trained
to kill people?

547
00:37:07.102 --> 00:37:08.478
Ooh-rah.

548
00:37:16.069 --> 00:37:17.654
How's your jumper shaping up?

549
00:37:17.738 --> 00:37:18.822
Hey.

550
00:37:19.740 --> 00:37:23.035
Can you take a look at this suicide note?
Most of it makes sense.

551
00:37:23.118 --> 00:37:26.872
but then it ends with.
"I can hear the Devil's footsteps draw near."

552
00:37:29.041 --> 00:37:32.461
Usually. suicide notes are either
all crazy or all rational.

553
00:37:32.503 --> 00:37:34.004
but this one's both.

554
00:37:34.421 --> 00:37:36.131
It's strange. isn't it?

555
00:37:38.050 --> 00:37:39.510
Yeah. it is.

556
00:37:44.306 --> 00:37:46.391
This one? Elevator key.

557
00:37:49.478 --> 00:37:50.687
Key's not catching.

558
00:37:50.812 --> 00:37:52.439
All right. Try the Halligan.

559
00:37:54.566 --> 00:37:56.235
Something's jamming it.

560
00:37:58.779 --> 00:37:59.863
Look. if I can--

561
00:37:59.947 --> 00:38:03.158
If I can get up there. I can maybe
figure out what's wrong with this thing.

562
00:38:06.787 --> 00:38:10.582
I'm a mechanic. I'm pretty good
with this sort of thing.

563
00:38:18.423 --> 00:38:21.802
He's trying to escape.
He's trying to escape.

564
00:38:21.844 --> 00:38:23.303
He's trying to escape!

565
00:38:23.345 --> 00:38:25.055
- He's trying to escape!
- Stop! Stop!

566
00:38:25.180 --> 00:38:27.349
Stop it!
Stop! What are you doing?

567
00:38:31.144 --> 00:38:32.437
What the hell are you doing?

568
00:38:32.521 --> 00:38:35.399
We're all gonna stay right here
until this thing is over.

569
00:38:35.482 --> 00:38:37.609
You knew what I was doing!
I told you what I was doing!

570
00:38:37.693 --> 00:38:39.027
I don't know you!

571
00:38:42.906 --> 00:38:45.033
It's not our policy
to discuss cases under review.

572
00:38:45.075 --> 00:38:48.120
It kind of damages the reputations
of our member businesses.

573
00:38:48.203 --> 00:38:49.872
Look. someone just killed him
on his way here.

574
00:38:49.913 --> 00:38:53.000
I need to know who knew he was coming here
and who wanted him dead.

575
00:38:54.376 --> 00:38:57.212
The line would stretch
around the block.

576
00:38:57.754 --> 00:38:59.548
The guy was a real scumbag.

577
00:38:59.756 --> 00:39:02.426
Three years ago. he started
one of those Ponzi schemes

578
00:39:02.551 --> 00:39:04.928
and when it collapsed.
a lot of people lost their asses.

579
00:39:05.220 --> 00:39:06.805
One guy even killed himself over it.

580
00:39:06.972 --> 00:39:08.724
Do you have a list of people
that got burned by him?

581
00:39:08.765 --> 00:39:10.767
- Yeah. the ones that filed.
- I'm gonna need it.

582
00:39:11.059 --> 00:39:14.062
So. what do you say we get
to know each other a little bit better?

583
00:39:14.771 --> 00:39:18.400
Here. Come on.
Frisk me. Search me.

584
00:39:18.442 --> 00:39:21.612
See that I'm not carrying
anything suspicious.

585
00:39:23.322 --> 00:39:24.406
Come on!

586
00:39:35.626 --> 00:39:37.127
You're next.

587
00:39:43.425 --> 00:39:45.302
There's a good chance one
of our people didn't sign in.

588
00:39:45.427 --> 00:39:46.595
How's that?

589
00:39:46.637 --> 00:39:48.013
'Cause that person might be
on this list.

590
00:39:48.096 --> 00:39:49.097
What's this?

591
00:39:49.181 --> 00:39:51.141
Our victim lost
a lot of people a lot of money.

592
00:39:51.183 --> 00:39:52.726
These are the ones
that filed complaints.

593
00:39:52.809 --> 00:39:55.604
The killer's probably smart enough
not to be on both lists.

594
00:39:55.687 --> 00:39:57.439
Look for the one
that didn't sign in.

595
00:39:57.940 --> 00:39:59.358
Did you just want video
of the guy who died.

596
00:39:59.441 --> 00:40:00.817
or also the girl that got hurt?

597
00:40:00.901 --> 00:40:02.444
All of it since they got in the car.

598
00:40:02.486 --> 00:40:03.529
Okay.

599
00:40:03.612 --> 00:40:04.780
Detective.

600
00:40:07.115 --> 00:40:08.492
You see?

601
00:40:09.576 --> 00:40:10.869
That's what you're talking about?

602
00:40:12.579 --> 00:40:14.498
Everybody believes in him
a little bit.

603
00:40:14.581 --> 00:40:17.042
even guys like you
who pretend they don't.

604
00:40:32.474 --> 00:40:33.809
What's this?

605
00:40:36.937 --> 00:40:39.439
An apology note left at the site
of a hit-and-run.

606
00:40:40.858 --> 00:40:44.027
My wife and son were killed
down on Bethlehem Pike five years ago.

607
00:40:46.280 --> 00:40:50.868
but that's okay.
because whoever did it is sorry.

608
00:40:52.327 --> 00:40:54.204
You can tell by the heartfelt apology

609
00:40:54.288 --> 00:40:56.081
on the back of a car wash coupon.

610
00:40:56.290 --> 00:40:59.209
So. no. I don't believe in the Devil.
We don't need him.

611
00:40:59.626 --> 00:41:02.045
People are bad enough by themselves.

612
00:41:03.672 --> 00:41:05.007
Stop the tape.

613
00:41:05.841 --> 00:41:07.050
Back it up.

614
00:41:07.509 --> 00:41:08.886
Faster. faster.

615
00:41:09.511 --> 00:41:10.971
There. Now. play it.

616
00:41:12.556 --> 00:41:14.558
She was acting like he grabbed her.

617
00:41:17.853 --> 00:41:19.813
What is she up to?

618
00:41:22.399 --> 00:41:25.235
Folks. do me a favor.
keep your hands off each other.

619
00:41:25.319 --> 00:41:28.238
Leave the police work to me.
I'll be in there any moment.

620
00:41:29.198 --> 00:41:30.657
Won't I?

621
00:41:52.387 --> 00:41:53.680
Stop it.

622
00:41:55.766 --> 00:41:58.310
I don't like him touching me.
He's touching me.

623
00:41:58.435 --> 00:41:59.645
I don't like it!

624
00:41:59.728 --> 00:42:00.854
Stop pushing him onto me.

625
00:42:01.188 --> 00:42:02.397
Stand back.

626
00:42:02.481 --> 00:42:03.690
Hell. no.
I know you're not doing

627
00:42:03.732 --> 00:42:05.067
what it looks like you're doing!

628
00:42:05.108 --> 00:42:06.735
Spray that in here.
you're gonna blind all of us.

629
00:42:06.860 --> 00:42:08.153
- I'll do it.
- Seriously. put it down.

630
00:42:08.237 --> 00:42:09.279
Lady...

631
00:42:15.869 --> 00:42:20.290
Dwight. where are you?
You gotta stop disappearing. seriously.

632
00:42:21.416 --> 00:42:22.501
<i>Dwight.</i>

633
00:42:22.626 --> 00:42:23.752
Hang on a sec.

634
00:42:24.253 --> 00:42:27.381
<i>Dwight. you gotta get us in that car
right now. Where are you?</i>

635
00:42:29.091 --> 00:42:30.801
I can't.

636
00:42:31.593 --> 00:42:33.345
<i>Dwight. I need you to stay on Walkie!</i>

637
00:42:33.428 --> 00:42:34.721
Man...

638
00:42:41.019 --> 00:42:43.230
Can you see this?
Huh? You see this?

639
00:42:46.984 --> 00:42:50.904
"Use by October 21. 1987."

640
00:42:50.946 --> 00:42:52.364
She was scared. Relax.

641
00:42:52.656 --> 00:42:54.408
She tried to pepper spray me. man!

642
00:43:03.208 --> 00:43:04.793
<i>Dwight. where are you?</i>

643
00:43:05.127 --> 00:43:06.712
We're being saved.

644
00:43:07.796 --> 00:43:09.506
Dwight. where are you?

645
00:43:11.967 --> 00:43:13.635
Come on. pick up.
Pick up!

646
00:43:13.719 --> 00:43:15.012
They hear something.

647
00:43:15.637 --> 00:43:18.015
They hear your guy
moving in the shaft.

648
00:43:18.390 --> 00:43:20.225
Then how come he's not answering?

649
00:43:20.517 --> 00:43:23.520
<i>Dwight? Dwight. this is serious.
You need to pick up. Dwight.</i>

650
00:43:25.022 --> 00:43:26.148
Thank you!

651
00:43:26.481 --> 00:43:28.859
<i>Pick up. Dwight. Pick up.</i>

652
00:43:34.656 --> 00:43:35.824
Oh. no.

653
00:43:36.825 --> 00:43:40.662
No. no. Hey! Hey! Hey!
Oh. no. Hey!

654
00:43:40.871 --> 00:43:42.706
Hey! You all right?

655
00:43:46.543 --> 00:43:48.295
- Hey!
- Come on.

656
00:43:48.504 --> 00:43:51.423
Come on! Hey!

657
00:44:14.905 --> 00:44:16.823
Dwight. where the hell are you. man?
Come on!

658
00:44:17.032 --> 00:44:18.825
What floor did Dwight
enter the shaft from?

659
00:44:18.951 --> 00:44:20.744
He entered from the roof.

660
00:44:23.539 --> 00:44:24.873
What are they looking at?

661
00:44:25.207 --> 00:44:27.543
Dwight. Dwight. pick up.

662
00:44:52.651 --> 00:44:56.446
Looks like he fell.
He's impaled right on top of the elevator.

663
00:44:56.488 --> 00:44:58.323
<i>Hurt real bad. Possibly dead.</i>

664
00:45:03.912 --> 00:45:05.873
Hey. Bowden. I think
the people in the elevator

665
00:45:05.914 --> 00:45:07.833
can hear our radios.

666
00:45:10.752 --> 00:45:12.254
Yeah. that's confirmed.

667
00:45:13.213 --> 00:45:14.756
<i>Can you switch to channel eight?</i>

668
00:45:15.174 --> 00:45:17.259
<i>The car's stuck on 21.</i>

669
00:45:17.384 --> 00:45:18.611
<i>Markowitz. tell the Fire Department</i>

670
00:45:18.773 --> 00:45:21.555
looks like they have to go 
through the wall on 21.

671
00:45:21.805 --> 00:45:24.850
This is Lustig.
You can't just go through the wall.

672
00:45:24.933 --> 00:45:25.934
<i>Sure we can.</i>

673
00:45:26.393 --> 00:45:28.228
That's why you have insurance.

674
00:45:31.523 --> 00:45:33.734
Fire command. go to eight. please.

675
00:45:38.155 --> 00:45:39.281
There she is.

676
00:45:39.323 --> 00:45:40.365
Sarah Caraway.

677
00:45:40.449 --> 00:45:42.618
We know the security temp
is Benjamin Larson

678
00:45:42.659 --> 00:45:43.702
and we know McCormick.

679
00:45:43.785 --> 00:45:45.662
What other names are unaccounted for?

680
00:45:46.288 --> 00:45:50.667
Jane something. Looks like "Kowski."
The older woman.

681
00:45:54.004 --> 00:45:55.672
Find me footage of this guy.

682
00:45:56.256 --> 00:45:57.799
This way. ma'am.

683
00:45:58.634 --> 00:46:00.010
- Let's go.
- All clear.

684
00:46:04.473 --> 00:46:06.308
Okay. this time slow.

685
00:46:13.482 --> 00:46:14.816
You gotta be kidding me.

686
00:46:14.858 --> 00:46:16.151
Did she just steal that lady's wallet?

687
00:46:16.318 --> 00:46:19.321
So Vince was a scam artist.
this woman Jane's a thief.

688
00:46:19.530 --> 00:46:22.866
Sarah there is a liar
and our guard is a thug.

689
00:46:23.242 --> 00:46:25.244
Quite the crew we have here.

690
00:46:26.328 --> 00:46:28.539
I still haven't seen this guy here.

691
00:46:32.584 --> 00:46:33.585
What was that?

692
00:46:34.127 --> 00:46:35.504
It's okay.
Hard drive crash.

693
00:46:35.587 --> 00:46:36.880
I got it. Number 2.

694
00:46:40.050 --> 00:46:41.134
Here we go.

695
00:46:43.303 --> 00:46:45.347
Any other angle on the lobby?

696
00:46:45.848 --> 00:46:47.558
Just the main entrance.

697
00:46:48.684 --> 00:46:49.852
There.

698
00:46:51.937 --> 00:46:53.814
Okay. rewind back.

699
00:46:54.857 --> 00:46:56.108
Faster.

700
00:46:58.026 --> 00:46:59.528
There he is. Stop it.

701
00:47:04.992 --> 00:47:06.410
Where's that satchel?

702
00:47:12.082 --> 00:47:15.252
He doesn't--
There's no satchel in the elevator.

703
00:47:16.587 --> 00:47:17.796
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

704
00:47:20.841 --> 00:47:22.176
Shit.

705
00:47:23.510 --> 00:47:24.761
Oh. no.

706
00:47:25.095 --> 00:47:26.430
What's happening?

707
00:47:28.724 --> 00:47:30.350
I can't take this anymore!

708
00:47:30.392 --> 00:47:32.311
Don't come near me.
any of you!

709
00:47:32.436 --> 00:47:34.396
Maybe. if I could just
check the wiring...

710
00:47:49.661 --> 00:47:51.580
What the hell's going on?

711
00:48:01.798 --> 00:48:04.968
Please. Please turn on the light.

712
00:48:06.762 --> 00:48:09.264
Turn on the lights!

713
00:48:23.487 --> 00:48:26.323
That's it.
Shut down the building.

714
00:48:26.823 --> 00:48:28.450
Bring everyone down to the lobby.

715
00:48:28.617 --> 00:48:30.244
Nobody comes in or out but us.

716
00:48:31.828 --> 00:48:33.622
Which guy do you think
is doing this?

717
00:48:33.664 --> 00:48:35.999
There are three people in there
and they're all capable.

718
00:48:36.375 --> 00:48:37.668
Well. she's not doing it.

719
00:48:38.043 --> 00:48:40.003
I'm ruling nobody out.

720
00:48:40.212 --> 00:48:42.172
Fire Department wants to know
if you have a shut-off valve

721
00:48:42.214 --> 00:48:43.966
before they get through the wall.
just in case.

722
00:48:44.174 --> 00:48:47.553
Yeah. it's in the basement.

723
00:48:50.055 --> 00:48:51.390
I'll go.

724
00:48:55.978 --> 00:48:57.646
They're bad people.
that's why they're here.

725
00:48:57.688 --> 00:49:00.899
No. two of them are here because
they just got on the wrong elevator.

726
00:49:00.983 --> 00:49:03.026
Yeah. and I just happened
to have the wrong job

727
00:49:03.110 --> 00:49:05.237
and you just happened
to take the wrong call.

728
00:49:12.661 --> 00:49:14.663
He never does this in secret.

729
00:49:16.623 --> 00:49:18.876
There's a reason we're the audience.

730
00:49:25.549 --> 00:49:27.259
Whoa. whoa. whoa.
Hold on. hold on.

731
00:49:27.467 --> 00:49:28.927
No one's getting in
this building right now.

732
00:49:29.011 --> 00:49:30.387
I know. I'm supposed
to meet somebody upstairs.

733
00:49:30.429 --> 00:49:32.431
You're gonna have to call them
and tell them you can't make it.

734
00:49:32.514 --> 00:49:33.932
Can you just tell me
what's happening?

735
00:49:34.016 --> 00:49:35.976
<i>He always kills the last victim</i>

736
00:49:36.018 --> 00:49:37.936
<i>in front of the person
they love most</i>

737
00:49:39.396 --> 00:49:41.273
<i>to make cynics of us all.</i>

738
00:49:41.481 --> 00:49:43.108
No. no. no.
Don't touch her.

739
00:49:43.192 --> 00:49:44.735
I'm not gonna leave her
just hanging there.

740
00:49:46.528 --> 00:49:48.113
Where you gonna put her?

741
00:49:48.238 --> 00:49:49.865
I haven't thought that far ahead.

742
00:49:56.914 --> 00:49:58.582
Funny how all this stuff
starts happening

743
00:49:58.707 --> 00:50:00.375
right after you start working here.

744
00:50:00.459 --> 00:50:01.960
Seems to me. you're the only one

745
00:50:02.044 --> 00:50:03.462
who knew where the cables are.

746
00:50:17.893 --> 00:50:19.478
What are you doing?

747
00:50:21.855 --> 00:50:23.774
Trying to close her eyes.

748
00:50:26.568 --> 00:50:30.113
That doesn't work. not until
they're dead for a few hours.

749
00:50:37.246 --> 00:50:38.956
Okay. you enter the building
with a satchel.

750
00:50:38.997 --> 00:50:41.458
You see a sign-in desk you wanna avoid.
Where do you go?

751
00:50:43.460 --> 00:50:45.420
- Restroom.
- Yep.

752
00:50:57.683 --> 00:50:58.934
Got it.

753
00:51:12.322 --> 00:51:14.408
Could those be used
to rig an elevator?

754
00:51:15.284 --> 00:51:20.372
I have no idea. but he doesn't sign in
and then he hides these?

755
00:52:01.371 --> 00:52:03.290
What the hell is that?

756
00:52:04.333 --> 00:52:05.792
I wish he'd stop.

757
00:52:13.842 --> 00:52:16.011
I don't even know your name.

758
00:52:22.351 --> 00:52:23.769
I'm Ben.

759
00:52:24.686 --> 00:52:26.230
I'm Sarah.

760
00:52:29.066 --> 00:52:30.901
I'm Tony.

761
00:52:44.665 --> 00:52:46.708
So where'd your claustrophobia go?

762
00:52:46.750 --> 00:52:47.835
Excuse me?

763
00:52:50.379 --> 00:52:54.383
I've never seen claustrophobia
come and go like that.

764
00:52:56.385 --> 00:52:58.387
- You trying to say something? Then say it.
- Yeah. yeah.

765
00:52:58.512 --> 00:52:59.930
Okay. I'm saying I didn't do this.

766
00:52:59.972 --> 00:53:01.807
and I very much doubt that she did.
so that leaves you.

767
00:53:02.683 --> 00:53:05.227
I'm saying I think
this claustrophobia thing...

768
00:53:06.353 --> 00:53:08.105
I think it's an act.

769
00:53:08.814 --> 00:53:10.816
Yeah. I'm saying I think you're a liar.

770
00:53:23.328 --> 00:53:24.580
Kill him. Ben!

771
00:53:27.082 --> 00:53:28.667
Kill him before he kills us!

772
00:53:29.960 --> 00:53:31.044
Kill him!

773
00:53:34.798 --> 00:53:35.799
Stop it! Stop!

774
00:53:37.467 --> 00:53:39.928
Stop it! Get us out!
Get us out! Get us out!

775
00:53:41.847 --> 00:53:45.225
Back away from each other now!
Get off!

776
00:53:46.310 --> 00:53:48.228
We're gonna keep you safe
and here's how.

777
00:53:48.270 --> 00:53:51.023
everyone get to a corner
and place your hands on the wall

778
00:53:51.106 --> 00:53:52.816
so everyone can see that
you're not up to anything.

779
00:53:53.317 --> 00:53:55.485
Go ahead. Do it!

780
00:53:58.614 --> 00:54:00.115
You won't have to keep this up long.

781
00:54:00.199 --> 00:54:02.117
The building is surrounded by police.

782
00:54:10.000 --> 00:54:13.921
In a hypothetical conversation
that I'm not really having.

783
00:54:14.880 --> 00:54:17.132
how would this story of yours end?

784
00:54:18.509 --> 00:54:20.093
They all die.

785
00:54:22.304 --> 00:54:23.680
That's it?

786
00:54:25.140 --> 00:54:26.308
Yeah.

787
00:54:28.018 --> 00:54:29.853
This is not your fault.

788
00:54:31.522 --> 00:54:34.024
They made the choices
that brought them here.

789
00:54:36.276 --> 00:54:38.237
Hey.
You're gonna love this.

790
00:54:38.320 --> 00:54:39.613
What have you got?

791
00:54:39.655 --> 00:54:41.031
She has a criminal record. too.

792
00:54:41.615 --> 00:54:44.159
Three counts of blackmailing
rich married men.

793
00:54:44.201 --> 00:54:45.494
Now where this gets interesting.

794
00:54:45.536 --> 00:54:47.996
is couple of years ago.
the arrests stopped. Guess why.

795
00:54:48.038 --> 00:54:49.081
Tell me.

796
00:54:49.164 --> 00:54:50.832
Well. her name is Sarah Caraway.

797
00:54:51.333 --> 00:54:52.543
"Caraway" Caraway?

798
00:54:52.626 --> 00:54:53.877
Yeah.
She married into the family.

799
00:54:53.961 --> 00:54:55.128
So she shoplifted an heir.

800
00:54:55.170 --> 00:54:56.296
Yeah. something like that. I guess.

801
00:54:56.338 --> 00:54:58.006
What's she doing here?

802
00:54:58.048 --> 00:54:59.341
According to the sign-in sheet.

803
00:54:59.383 --> 00:55:02.845
she was gonna see a lawyer
on 42 named Wayne Kazan.

804
00:55:04.179 --> 00:55:06.640
Excuse me. Excuse me.

805
00:55:07.349 --> 00:55:10.561
Hey. listen up!
Quiet down! Quiet down!

806
00:55:11.854 --> 00:55:13.230
Hey. quiet!

807
00:55:14.231 --> 00:55:15.732
Philadelphia P.D.!

808
00:55:16.817 --> 00:55:18.360
I'm looking for a Wayne Kazan.

809
00:55:18.443 --> 00:55:19.987
Is there a Wayne Kazan down here?

810
00:55:20.028 --> 00:55:21.697
Yeah.

811
00:55:21.780 --> 00:55:23.031
Excuse me.

812
00:55:23.323 --> 00:55:26.535
Heads up. Did you have
a meeting today with a Sarah Caraway?

813
00:55:27.536 --> 00:55:28.745
I don't know.
Do you have a subpoena?

814
00:55:28.829 --> 00:55:30.539
Come on. you can tell me that much.

815
00:55:30.789 --> 00:55:32.374
I might have. Why?

816
00:55:32.541 --> 00:55:35.419
She was attacked.
Who has motive to hurt her?

817
00:55:35.627 --> 00:55:37.212
Well. you know I can't divulge
personal information.

818
00:55:37.296 --> 00:55:38.422
Come on. man.
Give me something.

819
00:55:38.505 --> 00:55:39.590
Give me something to work with here.

820
00:55:39.673 --> 00:55:41.008
I'm trying to save
your client's life.

821
00:55:42.009 --> 00:55:43.468
Come here.

822
00:55:46.388 --> 00:55:48.265
I guess I'd do
what you guys normally do

823
00:55:48.307 --> 00:55:50.142
and start with
the person closest to her.

824
00:55:51.810 --> 00:55:53.187
- Thanks.
- And just so you know.

825
00:55:53.854 --> 00:55:56.106
my specialty is forensic accounting.

826
00:55:58.400 --> 00:56:00.777
Markowitz. get Mrs. Caraway's husband
on the phone.

827
00:56:07.159 --> 00:56:08.702
Should be okay now.

828
00:56:17.002 --> 00:56:18.712
All right. get in there.

829
00:56:37.606 --> 00:56:40.484
I might have found the problem.
It's a bad wire.

830
00:56:40.567 --> 00:56:42.986
Looks like it could be
shorting out the circuits.

831
00:57:03.215 --> 00:57:04.216
Okay.

832
00:57:07.970 --> 00:57:10.347
Easy. Easy.

833
00:57:10.681 --> 00:57:11.890
That's it.

834
00:57:31.618 --> 00:57:32.953
Yeah. I'm fine.

835
00:57:33.287 --> 00:57:35.664
Vasquez. we're gonna need
the large Target saw up here

836
00:57:35.706 --> 00:57:36.707
as fast as you can bring it.

837
00:57:44.506 --> 00:57:45.924
<i>Look. we need two more on 21.
okay. guys?</i>

838
00:57:46.008 --> 00:57:47.885
Any luck getting hold
of the husband?

839
00:57:47.926 --> 00:57:48.927
No. not yet.

840
00:57:49.011 --> 00:57:51.430
I called his office and his secretary
said he'd call me right back.

841
00:57:55.934 --> 00:57:57.728
Back up! Heads up. heads up!
Come on!

842
00:57:57.769 --> 00:57:58.937
Heads up! Back up!

843
00:57:59.021 --> 00:58:01.398
Move out of the way!
Get away! Back up!

844
00:58:01.440 --> 00:58:03.233
What happened?
Anybody see what happened?

845
00:58:03.275 --> 00:58:04.276
Medic!

846
00:58:04.359 --> 00:58:05.360
He came through the door.

847
00:58:05.611 --> 00:58:07.654
Breathe. Breathe.

848
00:58:08.113 --> 00:58:09.406
Lustig.

849
00:58:09.907 --> 00:58:12.326
Back away!
Back away! Move back!

850
00:58:12.367 --> 00:58:15.495
Get everybody back.
Back away!

851
00:58:33.555 --> 00:58:35.015
Put your hands back on the wall.

852
00:58:35.140 --> 00:58:36.308
It hurts.

853
00:58:40.646 --> 00:58:43.023
Put your hands back up on that wall.

854
00:58:46.568 --> 00:58:47.778
Or what?

855
00:58:51.323 --> 00:58:53.492
Just leave her alone.
She's in pain.

856
00:58:53.742 --> 00:58:55.994
Don't you see what she's doing?

857
00:58:57.120 --> 00:58:58.789
Chick's a twist.

858
00:58:59.373 --> 00:59:00.624
What are you talking about?

859
00:59:00.666 --> 00:59:03.669
Yeah. that's what we used to call
people like her in the Marines.

860
00:59:04.586 --> 00:59:07.714
Suddenly out of the blue. everybody
would start fighting with each other.

861
00:59:07.798 --> 00:59:10.217
Tempers would flare.
people would start getting hurt.

862
00:59:10.259 --> 00:59:14.471
But then we realized
it's just the new guy

863
00:59:15.180 --> 00:59:17.266
telling everybody
what other people said.

864
00:59:17.349 --> 00:59:19.643
stirring shit up
where there wasn't any.

865
00:59:21.728 --> 00:59:25.774
Until one night when we beat
the living shit out of that twist.

866
00:59:27.776 --> 00:59:30.571
And then. just like that.

867
00:59:32.948 --> 00:59:34.908
everything would go back to normal.

868
00:59:37.077 --> 00:59:38.912
Are you threatening me?

869
00:59:39.288 --> 00:59:41.874
I just want you to know
that I know.

870
00:59:43.667 --> 00:59:46.295
Why don't you just shut up
and keep your hands on the wall?

871
01:00:03.478 --> 01:00:05.439
<i>Sarah Caraway's husband
won't talk to us.</i>

872
01:00:05.480 --> 01:00:06.523
<i>He lawyered up.</i>

873
01:00:06.607 --> 01:00:09.234
Her lawyer told me
she's locating all his money.

874
01:00:09.568 --> 01:00:11.737
I bet she's about to leave him
and he might know it.

875
01:00:12.070 --> 01:00:13.864
That would definitely
give him motive to kill her.

876
01:00:14.239 --> 01:00:15.365
<i>But if he's trying to kill his wife.</i>

877
01:00:15.449 --> 01:00:17.117
<i>why are Jane Kowski
and Vince McCormick dead?</i>

878
01:00:17.201 --> 01:00:18.452
This is Matt with Caraway Security.

879
01:00:18.827 --> 01:00:20.120
I need someone from maintenance

880
01:00:20.162 --> 01:00:21.413
to come down
and shut the bay doors.

881
01:00:23.999 --> 01:00:27.669
Sarah Caraway's husband doesn't own
Caraway Security. does he?

882
01:00:28.712 --> 01:00:30.088
Meet me in the office!

883
01:00:40.724 --> 01:00:42.017
He's not done yet.

884
01:00:42.100 --> 01:00:43.644
It's the Kensington sniper
all over again.

885
01:00:44.019 --> 01:00:45.395
What's a Kensington sniper?

886
01:00:46.146 --> 01:00:48.690
A few years ago. a guy shot four strangers
and then his own wife.

887
01:00:48.774 --> 01:00:50.734
trying to make a personal killing
look like a serial.

888
01:00:50.776 --> 01:00:53.028
The guard works for the woman's husband.

889
01:00:53.070 --> 01:00:54.696
I think the two victims
were just a decoy.

890
01:00:54.738 --> 01:00:55.864
The guard is gonna kill her.

891
01:00:55.989 --> 01:00:57.115
I need to be
in that elevator right now!

892
01:00:57.199 --> 01:00:58.534
- Move!
- Right.

893
01:01:02.037 --> 01:01:03.539
Please don't let him kill me. Ben.

894
01:01:03.622 --> 01:01:05.040
I won't.

895
01:01:05.582 --> 01:01:08.544
Come over here next to me
and I'll keep you safe.

896
01:01:10.295 --> 01:01:12.172
Don't worry. Come on.

897
01:01:17.845 --> 01:01:19.096
<i>Hold up your cellphones.</i>

898
01:01:19.179 --> 01:01:20.931
<i>Use the screens as flashlights.</i>

899
01:01:23.559 --> 01:01:24.726
<i>Don't let it go dark in there.</i>

900
01:01:24.810 --> 01:01:26.103
Keep the light on each other.

901
01:01:26.144 --> 01:01:27.813
<i>Keep shining it all
around the elevator.</i>

902
01:01:39.157 --> 01:01:41.702
Don't you do it.
Don't you do it.

903
01:02:01.597 --> 01:02:03.599
It just doesn't make any sense.

904
01:02:05.642 --> 01:02:07.686
Oh. my God. It is you.

905
01:02:10.022 --> 01:02:11.523
Please. lady.

906
01:02:12.107 --> 01:02:15.235
They can't hear you.
You don't have to pretend anymore.

907
01:02:15.611 --> 01:02:17.487
We both know who did this.

908
01:02:19.156 --> 01:02:20.824
Yeah. we do.

909
01:02:31.710 --> 01:02:34.880
<i>Put down the glass
and get your hands on the wall now!</i>

910
01:02:36.131 --> 01:02:37.299
I should kill you right now.

911
01:02:37.382 --> 01:02:39.426
I should kill you right now
before you try anything else.

912
01:02:39.468 --> 01:02:40.802
I should cut you right now.

913
01:02:40.844 --> 01:02:43.514
And what'll be your defense? Huh?

914
01:02:44.598 --> 01:02:46.892
"She killed them all.
so I had to kill her"?

915
01:02:46.975 --> 01:02:49.144
Yeah. something like that.

916
01:02:49.311 --> 01:02:51.230
You take me down.

917
01:02:52.147 --> 01:02:55.984
they're pinning all of this on you
and you know it.

918
01:02:57.402 --> 01:02:59.905
A big. tough guy like yourself.

919
01:03:02.407 --> 01:03:03.867
This is what he does.

920
01:03:04.159 --> 01:03:06.119
He wants us to doubt everything.

921
01:03:06.328 --> 01:03:07.621
Markowitz.

922
01:03:08.163 --> 01:03:10.040
- <i>Markowitz?</i>
- We're getting close. boss.

923
01:03:11.917 --> 01:03:13.377
Hurry up!

924
01:03:13.836 --> 01:03:15.337
How would I do it?

925
01:03:15.712 --> 01:03:17.047
Do what?

926
01:03:18.382 --> 01:03:22.010
According to your story.
how would I save them?

927
01:03:24.054 --> 01:03:25.973
There's no easy answer.

928
01:03:27.349 --> 01:03:29.184
You're never gonna get these people

929
01:03:29.309 --> 01:03:31.144
to see themselves
as they really are

930
01:03:32.229 --> 01:03:34.356
'cause it's the lies
that we tell ourselves.

931
01:03:34.648 --> 01:03:36.483
they introduce us to him.

932
01:03:48.537 --> 01:03:49.913
Look at what you're doing.

933
01:03:50.873 --> 01:03:52.207
<i>Don't think just because I'm a cop</i>

934
01:03:52.249 --> 01:03:54.376
<i>I don't know what you're
going through right now.</i>

935
01:03:57.671 --> 01:03:59.214
I've been to hell.

936
01:04:02.801 --> 01:04:05.137
Six months ago. I...

937
01:04:08.182 --> 01:04:11.727
checked into a hotel
and I nearly drank myself to death.

938
01:04:12.728 --> 01:04:16.148
The thing is.
when you're self-destructing.

939
01:04:16.231 --> 01:04:18.233
it looks like it's the world's fault.

940
01:04:18.317 --> 01:04:21.778
Like you're dealt a series of shit hands.
but that's not real.

941
01:04:22.196 --> 01:04:25.532
Okay? It was all on me.
All of it.

942
01:04:26.658 --> 01:04:29.745
I realized my only way out of hell
was to take responsibility

943
01:04:29.828 --> 01:04:31.371
<i>for what I had become.</i>

944
01:04:34.041 --> 01:04:36.376
You are responsible for this.

945
01:04:36.585 --> 01:04:37.878
You realize that. don't you?

946
01:04:37.920 --> 01:04:40.422
Take responsibility
for what you're doing.

947
01:04:42.758 --> 01:04:44.301
Put down the glass.

948
01:04:47.346 --> 01:04:49.014
<i>Put down the glass.</i>

949
01:04:56.605 --> 01:04:58.982
I'll put this down if you do. too.

950
01:04:59.816 --> 01:05:01.318
Okay?

951
01:05:02.694 --> 01:05:04.530
We'll call a truce.

952
01:05:29.179 --> 01:05:30.472
<i>Good.</i>

953
01:05:31.306 --> 01:05:33.058
<i>You're doing the right thing.</i>

954
01:05:36.645 --> 01:05:39.648
Sir. we found a woman who thinks
she knows someone in the elevator.

955
01:05:40.065 --> 01:05:41.400
Send her in.

956
01:05:43.277 --> 01:05:44.361
No.

957
01:05:45.195 --> 01:05:46.780
Get in there!
Get in there! Now!

958
01:05:47.698 --> 01:05:49.032
We're through!

959
01:06:33.118 --> 01:06:34.244
This is the woman
I was telling you--

960
01:06:34.369 --> 01:06:35.871
Hold her outside!

961
01:06:35.913 --> 01:06:37.039
Tony.

962
01:06:39.833 --> 01:06:40.876
You know him?

963
01:06:41.168 --> 01:06:44.004
He's my fianc�.
He had a job interview here today

964
01:06:44.087 --> 01:06:46.089
and he didn't want
to bring his tools in with him.

965
01:06:46.173 --> 01:06:47.174
I was late picking them up.

966
01:06:47.299 --> 01:06:48.383
Tony what?

967
01:06:48.467 --> 01:06:49.927
Janekowski. Tony Janekowski.

968
01:06:55.557 --> 01:06:58.143
Jane Kowski is Janekowski?

969
01:06:59.269 --> 01:07:01.772
He signed in. Then who is--

970
01:07:02.105 --> 01:07:04.483
Come on. breathe. Right there.
Come on. breathe.

971
01:07:05.275 --> 01:07:08.946
Breathe! Come on. come on.
Please breathe.

972
01:07:12.533 --> 01:07:14.284
It's her! It's her.

973
01:07:16.537 --> 01:07:17.829
Get in there already.

974
01:07:20.207 --> 01:07:21.959
- Who are you?
- Today?

975
01:07:22.918 --> 01:07:24.294
I'm an old woman.

976
01:07:25.128 --> 01:07:27.214
Grab her the moment you get in.

977
01:07:27.756 --> 01:07:31.134
Are you ready for your turn. Anthony?

978
01:09:20.911 --> 01:09:22.246
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

979
01:09:23.121 --> 01:09:24.581
I'm sorry.

980
01:09:24.831 --> 01:09:27.209
The whores. the liars.
the cheats and the deserters.

981
01:09:27.251 --> 01:09:29.002
it's always the same thing.

982
01:09:29.670 --> 01:09:31.922
You know who I am now.

983
01:09:32.172 --> 01:09:33.549
Yes?

984
01:09:36.885 --> 01:09:37.928
Take me.

985
01:09:38.011 --> 01:09:39.054
I intend to.

986
01:09:39.096 --> 01:09:42.933
No. take me instead.
I deserve this.

987
01:09:43.600 --> 01:09:45.060
You don't believe that.

988
01:09:45.143 --> 01:09:47.688
Yes. Yeah. I do.

989
01:09:49.231 --> 01:09:50.858
I should never have left.

990
01:09:50.899 --> 01:09:53.569
It's my fault.
It's all my fault.

991
01:09:53.652 --> 01:09:55.904
You think you can make
some kind of bargain?

992
01:09:56.363 --> 01:09:57.906
Take me instead. Please.

993
01:09:58.073 --> 01:09:59.074
Stop saying that!

994
01:10:15.716 --> 01:10:17.342
You think this will
make you good?

995
01:10:17.509 --> 01:10:18.760
You're not good.

996
01:10:18.927 --> 01:10:20.095
I know.

997
01:10:20.262 --> 01:10:22.222
You think you can make up
for the choices you made?

998
01:10:23.515 --> 01:10:24.683
No.

999
01:10:26.268 --> 01:10:27.936
You think you can be forgiven?

1000
01:10:28.228 --> 01:10:29.438
No.

1001
01:10:31.023 --> 01:10:32.024
Channel eight.

1002
01:10:33.192 --> 01:10:36.195
I killed a mother and her son
on Bethlehem Pike

1003
01:10:36.278 --> 01:10:37.654
five years ago.

1004
01:10:38.947 --> 01:10:39.990
Uh.

1005
01:10:40.616 --> 01:10:43.452
It was a hit-and-run
and I was never caught.

1006
01:10:48.749 --> 01:10:50.292
I'm so sorry.

1007
01:11:17.319 --> 01:11:18.320
No.

1008
01:11:33.210 --> 01:11:34.336
Damn.

1009
01:11:35.754 --> 01:11:37.548
I really wanted you.

1010
01:12:02.990 --> 01:12:04.992
Come on. come on. come on!

1011
01:12:14.001 --> 01:12:15.335
Where is she?

1012
01:12:16.211 --> 01:12:17.880
Where'd she go?

1013
01:13:29.117 --> 01:13:30.619
I'll take him in.

1014
01:14:12.494 --> 01:14:15.497
That was my family
on Bethlehem Pike.

1015
01:14:19.459 --> 01:14:21.128
That was my son.

1016
01:14:32.139 --> 01:14:34.349
I've been waiting for this moment
for five years.

1017
01:14:34.433 --> 01:14:36.727
All the things I'd say to you

1018
01:14:38.228 --> 01:14:39.605
and what I'd do.

1019
01:14:47.029 --> 01:14:48.530
The thing is...

1020
01:14:54.244 --> 01:14:55.829
I forgive you.

1021
01:15:01.418 --> 01:15:06.548
<i>After my mother would finish her story.
she would always comfort us.</i>

1022
01:15:07.257 --> 01:15:09.384
<i>"Don't worry." she'd say.</i>

1023
01:15:10.260 --> 01:15:15.098
<i>"If the Devil is real.
